horizpa.horizpar: Built from corner information - Corner horizontal accuracy citation: Horizontal accuracy has been maintained to the highest degree possible without utilizing additional field surveys. For each corner, extensive searches of record information and subsequent selection of "best" sources were used to locate corners. No field surveys were conducted to find questionable corners. Where the only information available was from original Government Plats, BLM-GCDB data was used where possible. If records identified multiple alternate positions for the same corner i, the County Surveyor determined which was to be used. This was primarily the case where two monuments were labeled as the same corner and were within 3 feet of each other.
